Package: wizrd
Type: Package
Title: Integration of Large Language Models (LLMs) into R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
		person(given = "Michael", family = "Lawrence",
		       role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "michafla@gene.com")
	   )
Description: Ride the LLM hype llama with an abstraction for configuring
	     and running models on top of various LLM backends,
	     commercially hosted or local. Craft parameterized
	     prompts. Chat using text and images. Stream chat
	     responses. Generate embeddings and realize the RAG to
	     riches dream. Implement tools using R functions and
	     instruct the model to call them. Wrap models as tools
	     callable by other models. Use cases include
	     generating code, guiding data exploration, and creating
	     documentation. Powered by S7.
License: MIT
